        <h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
        <div style="background:#f8f9fa;padding:20px;border-radius:10px;margin:20px 0;">
          <h4>Will this yellow in sunlight like old epoxy?</h4>
          <p><strong>No</strong> — our polyaspartic top coat is UV-stable and specifically designed to withstand garage door exposure.</p>

          <h4>Will hot tires peel the coating?</h4>
          <p><strong>No.</strong> We use true 100% solids epoxy as a base coat with the flakes and a polyaspartic topcoat, which chemically bonds to concrete and won't lift from heat transfer.</p>

          <h4>Can it be done in one day?</h4>
          <p><strong>Technically, yes</strong> — but we don't believe in rushing the job. A true chemical bond needs full cure time before sealing.</p>

          <h4>Is it slippery?</h4>
          <p>Our flakes naturally add grip. We also offer anti-slip additives for extra traction if needed.</p>

          <h4>How long does it last?</h4>
          <p>It will last the life of the concrete. With basic care many customers never have to recoat.</p>

          <h4>How do I clean it?</h4>
          <p>Just hose off, mop, or use a mild degreaser. It's sealed, stain-resistant, and waterproof.</p>
        </div>

